<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <style>
        .a{
            color: blue;
        }
        .b{
            color: chocolate;
        }
        .c{
            color: blueviolet;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1 class="b" id="p">Guna</h1>
    <h2 class="c" id="q">Anusha</h1>
    <h3 class="a" id="r">Chiru</h1>
    <h2 class="b">Purushotham</h1>
    <script>
        //let x=document.getElementById("p")
            //console.log(x)

        let x=document.getElementsByClassName("a")
            console.log(x)
        for(let i=0;i<=x.length;i++){
            console.log(x[i])
        }

        let y=document.getElementsByClassName("b")
            console.log(y)
        for(let i=0;i<=y.length;i++){
            console.log(y[i])
        }

        let z=document.getElementsByTagName('h2')
        
        for(let i=0;i<=z.length;i++){
            console.log(z[i])
        }


    </script>
</body>
</html>

DOM( document object model):
It is a programming interface in web development, that allows us to interact and manipulate (change) the html document.
When the web page is loaded, the browser creates the dom of the webpage.
When an html file is loaded into browser, the javascript cannot understand html document directly.
DOM: is basically representation of same html document but in tree like structure composed of objects.
HTML dom allows javascript to access (to get) and modify all elements in html.
Keypoints:
Structure: the dom represents the structure of html document as tree; each node in a tree represents element, attribute,text.
Manipulation: using js, you can interact with elements(buttons,h,p) we can modify, add, remove element.
Event handling
World wide web cosortium
<html>
